  <script is:inline>
    (function() {
      // ── Real guest reviews pool (5-star only) ──────────────────────────────
      var REVIEWS = [
        { q: "Private launch into the Madawaska. Perfect location to access different sections of river and some local lakes. Also took in a hike just three kilometres down the road. The cottage is quite spacious and we found it exactly as advertised.", n: "Fraoch · Ottawa" },
        { q: "A little piece of paradise. Comfortable, spacious, and enjoyed the canoe. Thanks for a great stay.", n: "Claire · Elora" },
        { q: "Luka was an absolutely fantastic host and so kind. His place was unpretentious, simple and comfortable — everything a good cottage should be. I got to reconnect with myself and nature while I was there and I left feeling refreshed and grateful.", n: "Michelle · Peterborough" },
        { q: "Always a pleasure staying here. It has become a yearly event. Can't wait to go back next year.", n: "Justin · Burlington" },
        { q: "We really enjoyed our stay at Owl's Nest. Lovely cabin with a well equipped kitchen and beautifully decorated space. The river is lovely and calm in the mornings — a doe and fawn came by to say hello one morning.", n: "Rachel · Strathroy" },
        { q: "Had a wonderful stay at this rustic and beautiful spot. The star gazing was top notch!! The water was perfect — paddling out on our SUP to jump into the current was refreshing and fun. The proximity to amazing hikes was appreciated.", n: "Sarah · Toronto" },
        { q: "Thoroughly enjoyed the place and the quiet surroundings…very impressed with the cleanliness and the details in the little things to make your stay great! Come ready to relax and unwind!", n: "Janice · Welland" },
        { q: "River flows right on the property and the surroundings are serene. When we arrived, the grass was tall and Luka arrived within an hour and cut it so we could enjoy the evening outside. An outstanding host.", n: "Aniruddha · Toronto" },
        { q: "Amazing stay yet again! We absolutely love this Airbnb. The location, the cleanliness, the value, the hospitality. Wonderful experience and perfect place to make memories. A definite must stay!", n: "Brittany · Windsor" },
        { q: "Lovely spot to chill out. The cottage is rustic but comfortable. The kitchen is well stocked. Great value. Very quiet — no sound of highway traffic. Bring your s'more kit!", n: "Kyla · Ottawa" },
        { q: "Very beautiful area, lots of space around the cottage giving good privacy and room for our dogs to play. The cottage itself was well stocked, comfy and cute.", n: "Zosia · St. Catharines" },
        { q: "All we wanted was to check out from the city and see the stars by a firepit and we got that and more. We particularly enjoyed the canoe, and there was surprisingly cheap gas at the store nearby.", n: "Atsushi · Toronto" },
        { q: "Check in was super easy. Location is very private and good swimming!! Cottage was very very clean and cozy! We will be back.", n: "Amanda" },
        { q: "The deck overlooks the Madawaska river and is ideal to unwind. Luka was friendly and always willing to help us and ensured we were comfortable. Any questions he will reply within a short time. We will come again.", n: "Eomal · Brampton" },
        { q: "This gem tucked on the Madawaska River is ideal: the cabin sits on a small hill overlooking the flowing river, peaceful and beautiful, cosy and cute. Luka is a terrific host — attentive and quickly responsive.", n: "Kelby · Toronto" },
        { q: "Fishing was awesome! Caught some huge catfish right off the dock. The cabin was clean, comfy, and had everything we needed. Luka was super friendly and helpful. We would definitely visit again!", n: "Emily · Niagara Falls" },
        { q: "Excellent location for canoeing the rapids on the Lower Madawaska. We did the section from below Slate Falls to the cottage three times. Next time we visit we'll run the full section from Aumonds Bay. We plan to return.", n: "Geoff · Knowlton" },
        { q: "Luka was a great host! Responsive and helpful! The place is so clean, has beautiful scenery and is private. We'll definitely recommend it to others and hope to come back again!", n: "Pat · Markham" },
        { q: "Spent the weekend and wished we could have spent a week. The cabin is amazing and the wood stove makes the experience. 100% recommend and family friendly.", n: "Jeanna · Bath" },
        { q: "A wonderful place to relax and recharge! Luka and Tori are friendly, responsive hosts. The cabin was everything we had hoped for.", n: "Angela" },
        { q: "The cottage was cozy and clean, the view of the river was beautiful. The pictures were accurate, Luka was flexible and friendly, and we enjoyed our stay.", n: "Beau" },
        { q: "My family and I had a great time — we will definitely be booking another stay. The location was very quiet and peaceful, we loved the fire pit and the little dock was great for fishing.", n: "Mylaine" },
        { q: "My friend and I were delighted with this comfortable cottage and especially the beautiful surroundings. A bonus is the proximity to two great hiking trails — Jameson Mountain and Griffith Uplands.", n: "Wendy · Killaloe" },
        { q: "We wanted a quiet place to get away from the city. This was the perfect little getaway! My favourite part of the day was having my morning coffee on the deck and listening to the sounds of nature!", n: "Allison" },
        { q: "Staying at Luka's cottage was a fantastic getaway. He even brought over firewood and a canoe for us to use. The cottage has private access to the river and everything was very clean. Highly recommended!", n: "Ron · Toronto" },
        { q: "We absolutely loved this peaceful little retreat! We even saw a moose regularly across the river! Luka was very easy to communicate with and responded to anything we required.", n: "Madisen · Belleville" },
        { q: "The view across the river was beautiful. We saw a moose grazing for over 2 hours one morning. Luka is a great host — I'd recommend this place to anyone wanting to get away and be surrounded by nature.", n: "Justin · Burlington" },
        { q: "Words can't describe how beautiful the cottage and property were. Luka was quick to respond to any questions we had. Everything listed was there and in excellent working order. Will be back for sure!", n: "Jason · Hamilton" },
        { q: "Calm, peaceful getaway tucked away in the midst of nature! Wonderful location, ample privacy and great amenities. Luka was a great host, very responsive and made sure we had a great stay!", n: "Shamanth · Bengaluru" },
        { q: "Such an amazing place and host! The view was scenic, the place was super clean, and Luka responded to queries with near lightning speed. Thank you so much!", n: "Chippy" },
        { q: "Five stars all around. The cottage was perfect, the view just as. Luka and his family went above and beyond — during a power outage they set us up in another cottage with a wood stove already roaring. I can't wait to come back.", n: "Carolyn · Ottawa" },
        { q: "The house is very nice and well equipped, the environment is superb, especially in autumn. Luka and his father are attentive hosts and communication was very easy.", n: "Audrey · Kingston" },
        { q: "We had a great time at Luka's cottage on Madawaska River. It is absolutely beautiful and we couldn't have asked for anything better! Looking forward to visiting again!", n: "Ayslin · Ottawa" },
        { q: "This place was absolutely perfect for our family — clean and had everything we were looking for! Went with our 2 and 4 year old and they loved spending so much time on the water!", n: "Jazzmin" },
        { q: "The cabin provided a perfect getaway. Very clean and comfortable, and the location is wonderfully peaceful and beautiful. Had a great time watching the blue jays swooping across the property in the morning.", n: "Lisa · Durango" },
        { q: "Very cozy and beautiful place to relax and enjoy nature by the quiet river.", n: "Majid" },
        { q: "Our family had an absolutely wonderful vacation here. Very private with gorgeous scenery and wildlife. We were in a heat wave and were very grateful to have an AC unit available. We will definitely return.", n: "April" },
        { q: "This cottage is cute as a button. It was clean and looked just as expected. Luka was friendly and helpful and quick to respond to messages.", n: "Janet" },
        { q: "The place was excellent, very serene and very peaceful. The cottage was equipped with a lot of things to make the experience great. Communication with the host was excellent.", n: "Pushkar · Markham" },
        { q: "Great place and host! Will more than likely be booking again this summer! Luka was nice enough to let us have a later checkout!", n: "Veronica" },
      ];

      // Shuffle and pick 5 random reviews
      function pickRandom(arr, n) {
        var pool = arr.slice();
        for (var i = pool.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
          var j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));
          var tmp = pool[i]; pool[i] = pool[j]; pool[j] = tmp;
        }
        return pool.slice(0, n);
      }
      var picked = pickRandom(REVIEWS, 5);
      document.querySelectorAll('.review-card').forEach(function(card, i) {
        card.querySelector('.review-quote').textContent = '“' + picked[i].q + '”';
        card.querySelector('.review-name').textContent = picked[i].n;
      });

      // ── Carousel ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      var cards = document.querySelectorAll('.review-card');
      var dots  = document.querySelectorAll('[data-dot]');
      var current = 0;
      function show(n) {
        cards[current].style.display = 'none';
        dots[current].style.opacity = '0.25';
        current = (n + cards.length) % cards.length;
        cards[current].style.display = 'block';
        dots[current].style.opacity = '1';
      }
      dots.forEach(function(d) { d.addEventListener('click', function() { show(+d.dataset.dot); }); });
      setInterval(function() { show(current + 1); }, 6000);

      // ── Calendar today (timezone-safe) ────────────────────────────────────
      var today = new Date();
      var ds = today.getFullYear() + '-' + String(today.getMonth()+1).padStart(2,'0') + '-' + String(today.getDate()).padStart(2,'0');
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-date="' + ds + '"]').forEach(function(el) {
        el.classList.add('cal-today');
      });
    })();
  </script>

  <script is:inline>
  (function() {
    // Sun rings, aurora, and zen mode are desktop-only — skip entirely on touch devices
    if (navigator.maxTouchPoints > 0) return;
    // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // SUN RINGS
    // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    var srCanvas = document.getElementById('sun-rings-canvas');
    var sunEl    = document.getElementById('sun-rings-wrap');
    var sunDisk  = document.getElementById('sun'); // for colour animation during compression
    if (!srCanvas || !sunEl) return;
    var srCtx = srCanvas.getContext('2d');

    var CS = 800, CS2 = CS / 2;
    var dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;
    srCanvas.width  = Math.round(CS * dpr);
    srCanvas.height = Math.round(CS * dpr);
    srCtx.setTransform(dpr, 0, 0, dpr, 0, 0);

    var rings = [
      { R: 68,  comps: [[3.5, 2, 0.0], [1.8, 3, 1.2], [1.0, 5, 0.6]] },
      { R: 104, comps: [[4.5, 2, 0.9], [2.2, 3, 2.1], [1.3, 4, 1.8]] },
      { R: 146, comps: [[5.5, 2, 1.7], [2.8, 3, 0.4], [1.6, 5, 2.9]] },
    ];
    var BASE_R = [68, 104, 146];

    var bowStates = rings.map(function() {
      return { engaged: false, theta: 0, pullAmt: 0, pulses: [] };
    });

    var SR_ENGAGE_DIST = 13, SR_SNAP_DIST = 50, SR_BOW_HW = 1.75; // wide bell — deformation spreads over most of the ring
    var SR_PULL_SCALE  = 0.28, SR_PULSE_SPEED = 0.022, SR_PULSE_DECAY = 0.0022;
    var SR_PULSE_HW0   = 0.55, NSR = 260;
    var srT = 0;
    var srStartTime = 0; // set on first drawSunRings call

    // ── Explosion state machine ───────────────────────────────────────────────
    var EX_PHASE      = 0;   // 0=idle  1=compress  2=explode
    var EX_PHASE_START = 0;  // performance.now() timestamp when current phase began
    var EX_T          = 0;  // ms elapsed in current phase — set each frame
    var COMPRESS_DUR  = 3800; // ms — pressure build
    var VIBRATE_START = 3150; // ms — rings shudder in final stretch
    var EXPLODE_DUR   = 1450; // ms — expansion after burst

    // Dense inner pressure rings: [startR, targetR, peakAlpha, lineWidth]
    var INNER = [
      [8,  52, 0.82, 2.4],
      [18, 68, 0.64, 1.9],
      [29, 85, 0.46, 1.5],
    ];

    // Exploding ring snapshots (filled at compress→explode transition)
    var exRings = []; // { R, speed, alpha, width, night }

    function angDiff(a, b) {
      return ((a - b) % (2 * Math.PI) + 3 * Math.PI) % (2 * Math.PI) - Math.PI;
    }
    function angBell(dt, hw) {
      if (Math.abs(dt) >= hw) return 0;
      var b = 0.5 * (1 + Math.cos(Math.PI * dt / hw));
      return b * b;
    }
    function ringWaveR(ring, theta, t) {
      var r = ring.R;
      for (var j = 0; j < ring.comps.length; j++) {
        var c = ring.comps[j];
        r += c[0] * Math.cos(c[1] * theta + 0.0018 * c[1] * t + c[2]);
      }
      return r;
    }
    function bowDeformR(bow, theta, t) {
      var res = 0;
      if (bow.engaged && Math.abs(bow.pullAmt) >= 0.4) {
        var d0 = angDiff(theta, bow.theta);
        res += bow.pullAmt * SR_PULL_SCALE * angBell(d0, SR_BOW_HW);
      }
      for (var p = 0; p < bow.pulses.length; p++) {
        var pulse = bow.pulses[p];
        var age = t - pulse.releaseT;
        var amp = pulse.releaseAmt * Math.exp(-age * SR_PULSE_DECAY);
        if (Math.abs(amp) < 0.25) continue;
        var hw = SR_PULSE_HW0 + age * 0.007;
        var ctrs = [pulse.theta - SR_PULSE_SPEED * age, pulse.theta + SR_PULSE_SPEED * age];
        for (var ci = 0; ci < 2; ci++) {
          var d2 = angDiff(theta, ctrs[ci]);
          if (Math.abs(d2) < hw) res += amp * 0.65 * angBell(d2, hw);
        }
      }
      return res;
    }

    // Draw a plain circle of radius r
    function plainCircle(r, color, width) {
      srCtx.beginPath();
      for (var i = 0; i <= 200; i++) {
        var theta = (i / 200) * 2 * Math.PI;
        var x = CS2 + r * Math.cos(theta), y = CS2 + r * Math.sin(theta);
        if (i === 0) srCtx.moveTo(x, y); else srCtx.lineTo(x, y);
      }
      srCtx.closePath();
      srCtx.strokeStyle = color;
      srCtx.lineWidth   = width;
      srCtx.stroke();
    }

    function drawSunRings() {
      if (!srStartTime) srStartTime = performance.now();
      srT = (performance.now() - srStartTime) * 0.06; // 60fps-equivalent ticks — frame-rate independent
      srCtx.clearRect(0, 0, CS, CS);
      var isNight = document.documentElement.classList.contains('night');

      // ── Phase 0: normal ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      if (EX_PHASE === 0) {
        bowStates.forEach(function(bow) {
          bow.pulses = bow.pulses.filter(function(p) {
            var age = srT - p.releaseT;
            return Math.abs(p.releaseAmt * Math.exp(-age * SR_PULSE_DECAY)) >= 0.25;
          });
        });
        var dayA = [0.72, 0.50, 0.34], nightA = [0.58, 0.38, 0.24], wids = [2.8, 2.0, 1.4];
        rings.forEach(function(ring, ri) {
          var bow = bowStates[ri];
          srCtx.beginPath();
          var first = true;
          for (var i = 0; i <= NSR; i++) {
            var theta = (i / NSR) * 2 * Math.PI;
            var r = ringWaveR(ring, theta, srT) + bowDeformR(bow, theta, srT);
            var x = CS2 + r * Math.cos(theta), y = CS2 + r * Math.sin(theta);
            if (first) { srCtx.moveTo(x, y); first = false; } else srCtx.lineTo(x, y);
          }
          srCtx.closePath();
          var a = isNight ? nightA[ri] : dayA[ri];
          srCtx.strokeStyle = isNight ? 'rgba(245,230,150,' + a + ')' : 'rgba(245,200,66,' + a + ')';
          srCtx.lineWidth = wids[ri];
          srCtx.stroke();
        });

      // ── Phase 1: compress — inner rings press outer rings outward ────────────
      } else if (EX_PHASE === 1) {
        EX_T = performance.now() - EX_PHASE_START;
        var prog  = Math.min(EX_T / COMPRESS_DUR, 1);
        var ease  = prog * prog * prog; // cubic — pressure crawls, then surges
        var push  = 30 * ease;

        // Vibration ramps up in the final stretch — pressure-cooker shudder
        var vProg  = EX_T >= VIBRATE_START ? (EX_T - VIBRATE_START) / (COMPRESS_DUR - VIBRATE_START) : 0;
        var vibAmp = vProg * 7;                     // grows 0→7px
        var vibHz  = 0.18 + vProg * 1.10;           // temporal frequency ramps up

        // Outer rings displaced outward, brightened, and shuddering
        var bDA = [0.72, 0.50, 0.34], bNA = [0.58, 0.38, 0.24], bW = [2.8, 2.0, 1.4];
        rings.forEach(function(ring, ri) {
          ring.R = BASE_R[ri] + push * (1 + ri * 0.14);
          var bow = bowStates[ri];
          srCtx.beginPath();
          var first2 = true;
          for (var i = 0; i <= NSR; i++) {
            var theta = (i / NSR) * 2 * Math.PI;
            // Fine high-frequency trembling — many small bumps around the ring
            // rather than low polygon modes (2x/3x) that look like shape-morphing
            var vib = vibAmp * (
              Math.sin(srT * vibHz       + theta * 8  + ri * 1.30) * 0.55 +
              Math.sin(srT * vibHz * 1.5 + theta * 13 + ri * 0.80) * 0.45
            );
            var r = ringWaveR(ring, theta, srT) + bowDeformR(bow, theta, srT) + vib;
            var x = CS2 + r * Math.cos(theta), y = CS2 + r * Math.sin(theta);
            if (first2) { srCtx.moveTo(x, y); first2 = false; } else srCtx.lineTo(x, y);
          }
          srCtx.closePath();
          var baseA = isNight ? bNA[ri] : bDA[ri];
          var a = baseA + prog * 0.28 + vProg * 0.22; // extra flash near burst
          srCtx.strokeStyle = isNight ? 'rgba(255,240,160,' + a + ')' : 'rgba(255,215,80,' + a + ')';
          srCtx.lineWidth   = bW[ri] * (1 + prog * 0.45 + vProg * 0.30);
          srCtx.stroke();
        });

        // Inner pressure rings — grow faster, flash brighter as vibration peaks
        INNER.forEach(function(ir) {
          var curR = ir[0] + (ir[1] - ir[0]) * prog;
          var a    = ir[2] * (0.20 + 0.80 * prog + vProg * 0.40);
          var w    = ir[3] * (1 + vProg * 0.90);
          plainCircle(curR, isNight ? 'rgba(255,245,155,' + a + ')' : 'rgba(255,220,75,' + a + ')', w);
        });

        if (EX_T >= COMPRESS_DUR) {
          // Snapshot all ring positions into exRings for the explode phase
          var eA = [0.66, 0.52, 0.42], eW = [2.3, 1.7, 1.3];
          exRings = [];
          rings.forEach(function(ring, ri) {
            exRings.push({ startR: ring.R + 3, R: ring.R + 3, speed: 2.2 + ri * 1.3, alpha: eA[ri], width: eW[ri], night: isNight });
            ring.R = BASE_R[ri]; // reset for when normal drawing resumes
          });
          INNER.forEach(function(ir, i) {
            exRings.push({ startR: ir[1] + 3, R: ir[1] + 3, speed: 3.8 + i * 1.0, alpha: ir[2] * 0.85, width: ir[3] * 0.75, night: isNight });
          });
          EX_PHASE = 2; EX_PHASE_START = performance.now(); EX_T = 0;
          if (sunDisk) sunDisk.style.filter = ''; // snap back — flash overlay takes over
          triggerSkyEffects(isNight);
          if (typeof window.triggerWaveRipple === 'function') window.triggerWaveRipple();
        }

      // ── Phase 2: explode — all rings fly outward and fade ────────────────────
      } else if (EX_PHASE === 2) {
        EX_T = performance.now() - EX_PHASE_START;
        var prog2 = Math.min(EX_T / EXPLODE_DUR, 1);
        exRings.forEach(function(er) {
          er.R = er.startR + er.speed * 87 * prog2 * (1 + 2.86 * prog2);
          var a = er.alpha * Math.pow(Math.max(0, 1 - prog2), 0.65);
          // Fade out as rings approach the canvas edge — no hard clip
          var edgeFade = er.R < CS2 * 0.68 ? 1 : Math.max(0, 1 - (er.R - CS2 * 0.68) / (CS2 * 0.32));
          a *= edgeFade;
          if (a < 0.01) return;
          plainCircle(er.R, er.night ? 'rgba(255,240,150,' + a + ')' : 'rgba(255,215,80,' + a + ')',
            Math.max(0.5, er.width * (1 - prog2 * 0.55)));
        });
        if (EX_T >= EXPLODE_DUR) {
          EX_PHASE = 3; EX_PHASE_START = performance.now(); EX_T = 0; exRings = [];
          rings.forEach(function(ring) { ring.R = 0; }); // start from centre
        }

      // ── Phase 3: reset — rings emanate outward from centre back to idle ───────
      } else if (EX_PHASE === 3) {
        EX_T = performance.now() - EX_PHASE_START;
        var RESET_DUR = 1400, RESET_STAGGER = 120; // ms
        var dayA3 = [0.72, 0.50, 0.34], nightA3 = [0.58, 0.38, 0.24], wids3 = [2.8, 2.0, 1.4];
        var allDone = true;
        // Prune dead bow pulses just like Phase 0 — keeps cursor interaction live during reset
        bowStates.forEach(function(bow) {
          bow.pulses = bow.pulses.filter(function(p) {
            var age = srT - p.releaseT;
            return Math.abs(p.releaseAmt * Math.exp(-age * SR_PULSE_DECAY)) >= 0.25;
          });
        });
        rings.forEach(function(ring, ri) {
          var rp = Math.max(0, Math.min((EX_T - ri * RESET_STAGGER) / RESET_DUR, 1));
          if (rp < 1) allDone = false;
          var re = 1 - (1 - rp) * (1 - rp) * (1 - rp); // easeOutCubic
          ring.R = BASE_R[ri] * re;
          var bow = bowStates[ri];
          var a = (isNight ? nightA3[ri] : dayA3[ri]) * Math.min(rp * 3, 1); // fade in quickly
          srCtx.beginPath();
          for (var i3 = 0; i3 <= NSR; i3++) {
            var th3 = (i3 / NSR) * 2 * Math.PI;
            // Smoothly ramp the natural shimmer + cursor deformation in along with the
            // ring's growth. At rp=0 it's a perfect circle (matches the explode-out look),
            // at rp=1 it's identical to Phase 0 — no visual snap when the phase ends.
            var shimmer = ringWaveR(ring, th3, srT) - ring.R;       // just the wave components
            var bowR    = bowDeformR(bow, th3, srT);
            var r3 = ring.R + (shimmer + bowR) * re;
            var x3 = CS2 + r3 * Math.cos(th3), y3 = CS2 + r3 * Math.sin(th3);
            if (i3 === 0) srCtx.moveTo(x3, y3); else srCtx.lineTo(x3, y3);
          }
          srCtx.closePath();
          srCtx.strokeStyle = isNight ? 'rgba(245,230,150,' + a + ')' : 'rgba(245,200,66,' + a + ')';
          srCtx.lineWidth = wids3[ri];
          srCtx.stroke();
        });
        if (allDone) { EX_PHASE = 0; EX_PHASE_START = 0; EX_T = 0; }
      }

      requestAnimationFrame(drawSunRings);
    }

    // ── Zen mode sky effects — solar flare flash + tidal-wave scheduling ──────
    // The sky waves themselves live in Layout.astro (sLayers in the wave canvas),
    // gated on the `zen-mode` class. We only handle the one-shot orange flash here
    // and kick off the periodic tidal waves while zen mode is active.
    var skyEl = null;
    var tidalInterval = null, tidalTimeout = null;

    function triggerSkyEffects(isNight) {
      if (skyEl && skyEl.parentNode) { skyEl.parentNode.removeChild(skyEl); skyEl = null; }
      if (tidalTimeout)  { clearTimeout(tidalTimeout);   tidalTimeout  = null; }
      if (tidalInterval) { clearInterval(tidalInterval); tidalInterval = null; }

      // Solar flare flash — bright orange burst that fades back to normal sky
      skyEl = document.createElement('div');
      skyEl.style.cssText = [
        'position:fixed', 'inset:0', 'z-index:40', 'pointer-events:none',
        'background:' + (isNight ? 'rgba(255,145,20,0.58)' : 'rgba(255,165,30,0.70)'),
        'mix-blend-mode:screen', 'opacity:0', 'transition:opacity 0.25s ease',
      ].join(';');
      document.body.appendChild(skyEl);
      requestAnimationFrame(function() { requestAnimationFrame(function() {
        skyEl.style.opacity = '1';
        setTimeout(function() {
          skyEl.style.transition = 'opacity 2.4s ease';
          skyEl.style.opacity = '0';
          setTimeout(function() {
            if (skyEl && skyEl.parentNode) skyEl.parentNode.removeChild(skyEl);
            skyEl = null;
          }, 2500);
        }, 300);
      }); });

      // First tidal wave at 15 s, then every 30 s after that — Layout.astro's
      // triggerTidalWave drives the river bowstring pool directly.
      tidalTimeout = setTimeout(function() {
        if (typeof window.triggerTidalWave === 'function') window.triggerTidalWave();
        tidalInterval = setInterval(function() {
          if (typeof window.triggerTidalWave === 'function') window.triggerTidalWave();
        }, 30000);
      }, 15000);
    }

    // ── Clear effects — called when zen mode is exited ────────────────────────
    window.clearSkyEffects = function() {
      if (skyEl) {
        skyEl.style.transition = 'opacity 1.4s ease';
        skyEl.style.opacity = '0';
        var _s = skyEl; skyEl = null;
        setTimeout(function() { _s.parentNode && _s.parentNode.removeChild(_s); }, 1500);
      }
      if (tidalTimeout)  { clearTimeout(tidalTimeout);   tidalTimeout  = null; }
      if (tidalInterval) { clearInterval(tidalInterval); tidalInterval = null; }
    };

    // ── Expose trigger to the global scope ───────────────────────────────────
    window.triggerSunExplosion = function() {
      if (EX_PHASE !== 0) return;
      EX_PHASE = 1; EX_PHASE_START = performance.now(); EX_T = 0;
      bowStates.forEach(function(bow) { bow.engaged = false; bow.pullAmt = 0; });
    };

    // ── Mouse interaction: ring bowstring (aurora is handled by Layout.astro) ─
    document.addEventListener('mousemove', function(e) {
      // Ring bowstring (idle + compression + reset — not during explosion burst)
      if (EX_PHASE === 2) return;
      var rect = sunEl.getBoundingClientRect();
      var cx = rect.left + rect.width  / 2;
      var cy = rect.top  + rect.height / 2;
      var dx = e.clientX - cx, dy = e.clientY - cy;
      var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);
      var theta = Math.atan2(dy, dx);
      rings.forEach(function(ring, ri) {
        var bow = bowStates[ri];
        var dfr = Math.abs(dist - ring.R);
        if (bow.engaged) {
          bow.theta = theta; bow.pullAmt = dist - ring.R;
          if (Math.abs(bow.pullAmt) >= SR_SNAP_DIST) {
            bow.pulses.push({ theta: bow.theta, releaseAmt: bow.pullAmt * SR_PULL_SCALE, releaseT: srT });
            bow.engaged = false; bow.pullAmt = 0;
          }
        } else if (dfr <= SR_ENGAGE_DIST) {
          bow.engaged = true; bow.theta = theta; bow.pullAmt = 0;
        }
      });
    });

    drawSunRings();
  })();
  </script>

